FL,434,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1784837925
OL,3,CSpecialist helicopter to be deployed
OL,4,Cto fight ongoing wildfire
OL,6,FNorth Wales Fire and Rescue Service
OL,7,Fsaid: "Resources remain in attendance
OL,8,Fat Rhinogydd mountains near Llyn Cwm
OL,9,FBychan, close to Harlech and on the
OL,10,FTrawsfynydd side of the mountain,
OL,11,Fwhere crews are monitoring the area,
OL,12,Flimiting fire spread and undertaking
OL,13,Freactive firefighting.
OL,15,F"Guidance has been given to local
OL,16,Fcommunities by North Wales Police and
OL,17,FNorth Wales Fire and Rescue Service in
OL,18,Frelation to maintaining situational
OL,19,Fawareness and keeping up to date with
OL,20,Fonline and local media communications.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,434,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1784837925
OL,3,CSpecialist helicopter to be deployed
OL,4,Cto fight ongoing wildfire
OL,6,F"Due to the dynamic nature of the
OL,7,Fincident, we have officers in
OL,8,Fattendance in strategic locations
OL,9,Facross the incident ground who are
OL,10,Fcontinually monitoring the site and
OL,11,Fconditions to ensure proactive actions
OL,12,Fare taken well in advance of any
OL,13,Fevacuation instructions."
OL,15,FThe fire service is continuing to
OL,16,Fmonitor conditions at the following
OL,17,Fsites as a precaution:
OL,19,F- Pentre Halkyn
OL,21,F- Mount Pleasant in Brymbo
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
